Uses of Package
br.com.henriquewilhelm.orbit

  • Classes in br.com.henriquewilhelm.orbit used by br.com.henriquewilhelm.orbit 
    Class and Description
    Calculator
    System Solar Calculator Note that the definition of civil, nautical, and astronomical twilight is defined respectively as 6, 12, and 18 degrees below the horizon.
    Calculator.Offset
    Account For Atmospheric Refraction
    Calculator.TestResult
    Test Result
    Coordinates
    This class joins the necessary variables to the calculations performed on each element of the solar system
    Event
    The Event class gathers the calculations of one element of the solar system (Sun, Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto) The calculations are: Rise and set Time HorizonToHorizonCrossing type Time meridianCrossing (noon) Time, antimeridianCrossing (Midnigth) position (rightAscention, declination, longitudeEcliptic and distance)
    Event.HorizonToHorizonCrossing
    /** Type of Horizon Crossing (NO_CHANGE_PREVIOUSLY_RISEN, NO_CHANGE_PREVIOUSLY_SET, ONLY_RISEN ONLY_SET, RISEN_AND_SET)
    GpsCoordinate
    GPS Coordinate (Latitude x Longitude)
    MoonEvent
    The class extends of Event class, gathers the calculations of Moon The calculations are: Rise and set Time, HorizonToHorizonCrossing type, Time meridianCrossing (noon), Time antimeridianCrossing (Midnigth), Position (rightAscention, declination, longitudeEcliptic and distance)
    PerigeeApogeeCalculator
    This program helps those who need to know stage, age, distance and position of the moon along the ecliptic on any date within several thousand years in the past or in the future.
    Position
    The Position class gathers the position of one element of the solar system (Sun, Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto) The calculations are: Position (rightAscention, declination, longitudeEcliptic and distance)
    Result
    This class gathered the results of calculations performed by the calculator of the solar system.
    Time
    The only reason this class exists is so that this reference algorithm can be translated slightly more easily to another language.
